The value is an mpz_class, so to use the GMP function, I need to get the underlying mpz_t. So maybe:

mpz_urandomm (value.get_mpz_t(), GetRandomState(), n.get_mpz_t());

Then that should set 'value' to a random number between 0 and n-1.

Yes, the GMP docs say mpz_urandomm (OP, STATE, N) stores a uniform random number in [0, N). Exactly what's needed. So the missing line is:

mpz_urandomm(value.get_mpz_t(), GetRandomState(), n.get_mpz_t());

I think that's it.
